{
  "texts": [
    "V. RESULTSWe evaluated the proposed hybrid classification model by utilizing loss, accuracy, precision, and F1-score metrics over training time.",
    "The precision graph examines how accurately the model was predicting the metric over all epochs.",
    "The accuracy variable would increase over training time, indicating that the model's abilities to predict gliomas increased over training time.The loss graph measures the predicted value vs actual value.",
    "A decreasing loss accounts for the model's ability to become more converged to sophisticated performance.",
    "The accuracy should be consistently high for reliable classification of glioma images."
  ]
}